ootballbox collapsible\n|round=Second leg\n|date=31 October 1996\n|time=20:00\n|team1=[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] {{flagicon|GRE}}\n|score=4\u20130\n|aggregatescore=6\u20130\n|report=[https://web.archive.org/web/20040430140443/http://www.uefa.com/Competitions/ECWC/AllTimeStatistics/season%3D1996/Round%3D155/match%3D53269/index.html Lineups]\n|team2={{flagicon|SLO}} [[NK Olimpija Ljubljana (defunct)|Olimpija Ljubljana]]\n|goals1=[[Toni Savevski|Savevski]] {{goal|5}}<br />[[Daniel Batista Lima|Batista]] {{goal|34}}<br />[[Christos Maladenis|Maladenis]] {{goal|80}}<br />[[Christos Kostis|Kostis]] {{goal|84}}\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[Nikos Goumas Stadium]], [[Athens]]\n|attendance=14,482\n|referee=[[Hermann Albrecht]] ([[German Football Association|Germany]])\n|result=W\n|stack=yes\n}}\n'''Quarter-finals'''\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|round=First leg\n|date=6 March 1997\n|time=20:30\n|team1=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] {{flagicon|FRA}}\n|score=0\u20130\n|report=[https://web.archive.org/web/20040618194313/http://www.uefa.com/Competitions/ECWC/AllTimeStatistics/season%3D1996/Round%3D156/match%3D53368/index.html Lineups]\n|team2={{flagicon|GRE}} [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|goals1=\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[Parc des Princes]], Paris\n|attendance=21,952\n|referee=[[Urs Meier]] ([[Swiss Football Association|Switzerland]])\n|result=D\n|stack=yes\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|round=Second leg\n|date=20 March 1997\n|time=20:15\n|team1=[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] {{flagicon|GRE}}\n|score=0\u20133\n|aggregatescore=0\u20133\n|report=[https://web.archive.org/web/20040618234305/http://www.uefa.com/Competitions/ECWC/AllTimeStatistics/season%3D1996/Round%3D156/match%3D53369/index.html Lineups]\n|team2={{flagicon|FRA}} [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]\n|goals1=\n|goals2=[[Patrice Loko|Loko]] {{goal|21||44||81}}\n|stadium=[[Nikos Goumas Stadium]], [[Athens]]\n|attendance=35,000\n|referee=[[Antonio Jes\u00fas L\u00f3pez Nieto|Antonio L\u00f3pez Nieto]] ([[Royal Spanish Football Federation|Spain]])\n|result=L\n|stack=yes\n}}\n\n===Greek Cup===\n====Final====\n\nThe 55th [[Greek Cup]] Final was played at the [[Karaiskakis Stadium|Georgios Karaiskakis Stadium]].\n\n{{footballbox|\ndate= April 16, 1997|\nteam1= AEK Athens|\nscore= 0 &ndash; 0|\nteam2= Panathinaikos|\ngoals1=<!-- Image with inadequate rationale removed:  [[File:Aekemblem.svg|90px]] -->|\ngoals2=<!-- Deleted image removed:  [[File:PAOemblem.svg|116px]] -->|\nstadium= [[Karaiskakis Stadium|Georgios Karaiskakis Stadium]], [[Piraeus]]|\nattendance= 21,926|\nreferee= Giorgos Psychomanis ([[Athens Prefecture|Athens]])|\n|penalties1=[[:el:\u03a7\u03ac\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03bf\u03c0\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03ae\u03c2|Kopitsis]] {{pengoal}}<br />[[Vassilis Borbokis|Borbokis]] {{pengoal}}<br />[[Demis Nikolaidis|Nikolaidis]] {{pengoal}}<br />[[Anton Dobo\u015f|Dobo\u015f]] {{pengoal}}<br />[[Elias Atmatsidis|Atmatsidis]] {{pengoal}}\n|penaltyscore=5 &ndash; 3\n|penalties2={{penmiss}} [[Krzysztof Warzycha|Warzycha]]<br />{{pengoal}} [[Kostas Konstantinidis|Konstantinidis]]<br />{{pengoal}} [[Georgios Georgiadis (football player)|Georgiadis]]<br />{{pengoal}} [[Dimitris Markos|Markos]]}}\n\n{| width=92% |\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n|| pattern_la        = \n| pattern_b        = \n| pattern_ra       = \n| pattern_sh       = \n| pattern_so        = _band_black\n| leftarm          =FFEF00\n| body             =FFEF00\n| rightarm         =FFEF00\n| shorts          =000000\n| socks           =FFEF00\n | title      = AEK\n}}\n|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _white_stripes\n| pattern_b  = _panathinaikosfc9596t1\n| pattern_ra = _white_stripes\n| pattern_sh = \n| pattern_so = _3_stripes_white\n| leftarm = 109252 | body = 109252 | rightarm = 109252 | shorts = 109252 | socks = 109252\n | title      = Panathinaikos\n}}\n|}\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size: 90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=\"center\"\n|colspan=\"4\"|''